========,1,preface.
The Z shell (zsh) is a Unix shell that can be used as an interactive login shell and as a powerful command interpreter for shell scripting.
Zsh is an extended Bourne shell with a large number of improvements, including some features of bash, ksh, and tcsh.
========,2,Origin.
Paul Falstad wrote the first version of zsh in 1990 while a student at Princeton University.
The name "zsh" derives from the name of Yale professor Zhong Shao (then an Assistant Professor at Princeton University) â€” Paul Falstad regarded Shao's login-id, "zsh", as a good name for a shell.
